    "updated_at": "2018-08-06T23:01:37Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The problem here is that `calldata` encoding for structs isn't defined yet in the encoder and `external` forces that. Using `public` will make it work because then it is handled internally as encoding from memory.\r\n\r\nThere must be an issue tracking this already.",
